      "content": "The feeling of being trapped and exhausted is all too real. While there's no definitive answer to what constitutes dignity in your situation, some people have found solace in finding quiet, stillness, and acceptance, rather than trying to fight the inevitable. It's a personal choice, but it may be worth considering whether the dignity you think you'll find in silence is different from the dignity you've been trying to cling to through suffering.",
